  "prompt": "What are the best movies of the last two decades?",
  "response": "Determining the \"best\" movies can be subjective, but several films from the last two decades have received critical acclaim, significant box office success, or have made a notable impact on popular culture. Here's a list of some of the standout films from the past 20 years (2003-2023), organized by decade:\n\n### 2000s (2003-2009)\n1. **The Lord of the Rings: The Return of the King (2003)** - Directed by Peter Jackson, this epic conclusion to the trilogy won 11 Academy Awards.\n2. **Eternal Sunshine of the Spotless Mind (2004)** - A unique take on love and memory directed by Michel Gondry and written by Charlie Kaufman.\n3. **The Dark Knight (2008)** - Christopher Nolan's superhero film featuring Heath Ledger's iconic portrayal of the Joker.\n4. **Slumdog Millionaire (2008)** - Directed by Danny Boyle, this film exploring fate and love won multiple Oscars.\n5. **Avatar (2009)** - James Cameron's visually groundbreaking film that became the highest-grossing film of all time (until recently).\n\n### 2010s (2010-2019)\n1. **Inception (2010)** - Another Nolan masterpiece that explores dreams within dreams.\n2. **The Social Network (2010)** - David Fincher's dramatization of the founding of Facebook.\n3. **Moonlight (2016)** - An Oscar-winning film directed by Barry Jenkins that delves into themes of identity and masculinity.\n4. **Get Out (2017)** - Jordan Peele's groundbreaking horror-comedy that provides a critique of race relations in America.\n5. **Parasite (2019)** - Directed by Bong Joon-ho, this South Korean film made history by winning the Best Picture Oscar.\n\n### 2020s (2020-2023)\n1. **Nomadland (2020)** - Chlo\u00e9 Zhao's film about a woman living as a modern nomad in the American West won several Oscars, including Best Picture.\n2. **Dune (2021)** - Denis Villeneuve\u2019s adaptation of Frank Herbert's novel received acclaim for its visuals and storytelling.\n3. **Everything Everywhere All at Once (2022)** - A genre-blending film that explores multiple realities, which garnered significant awards attention.\n4. **Top Gun: Maverick (2022)** - A sequel that became a massive box office success and resonated with audiences for its nostalgia and action.\n5. **Oppenheimer (2023)** - Christopher Nolan\u2019s biopic about J. Robert Oppenheimer and the creation of the atomic bomb, acclaimed for its storytelling and performances.\n\n### Honorable Mentions\n- **Mad Max: Fury Road (2015)**\n- **The Shape of Water (2017)**\n- **Spider-Man: Into the Spider-Verse (2018)**\n- **1917 (2019)**\n- **All Quiet on the Western Front (2022)**\n\nThis list highlights just a fraction of the exceptional films that have emerged in the last two decades, spanning various genres and styles.",
